FuncDef: This command configures a range of encapsulation values.

ParaDef.Info: Specifies a range of encapsulation values on a port to be synchronized with a multi-chassis peer. Values-Dot1Q|start-qtag-end-qtag|, |start-qtag|0 to 4094, |end-qtag|0 to 4094, QinQ|qtag1.start-qtag2.end-qtag2-start-qtag1.*-end-qtag1.*|, |qtag1|1 to 4094, |start-qtag1|1 to 4094, |end-qtag1|1 to 4094, |start-qtag2|0 to 4094, |end-qtag2|0 to 4094.
Specifies a synchronization tag up to 32 characters in length to be used while synchronizing this encapsulation value range with the multi-chassis peer.
